President Obama held a national security meeting this morning to discuss the military operations in Libya. The meeting included National Security Advisor Tom Donilon, Secretary of State Hillary Clinton, Secretary of Defense Bob Gates, AFRICOM Commander General Carter Ham, and Deputy National Security Advisor Denis McDonough. General Ham provided a briefing on the U.S. military operations in Libya, and the President expressed his gratitude to him and the U.S. Armed Forces for their efforts in enforcing UN Security Council Resolution 1973. The President also discussed ongoing consultations on the situation in Libya.